Package: inflateR
Title: Inflation Adjustment for Historical Currency Values
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Charles", "Coverdale", email = "charlescoverdale@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Convert historical monetary values into their present-day equivalents
    using bundled CPI (Consumer Price Index) data sourced from the World Bank
    Development Indicators. Supports British pounds (GBP), Australian dollars (AUD),
    US dollars (USD), Euro (EUR), Canadian dollars (CAD), Japanese yen (JPY),
    Chinese yuan (CNY), and Swiss francs (CHF). Currency codes and country names
    are both accepted as input.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
URL: https://github.com/charlescoverdale/inflateR
BugReports: https://github.com/charlescoverdale/inflateR/issues
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
